abstract: Senior bankers and regulators across Europe are worried that markets could misinterpret the outcome of a test of how resilient European banks are to economic shocks, The Financial Times reported.
snippet: Senior bankers and regulators across Europe are worried that markets could misinterpret the outcome of a test of how resilient European banks are to economic shocks, The Financial Times reported.
lead_paragraph: Senior bankers and regulators across Europe are worried that markets could misinterpret the outcome of a test of how resilient European banks are to economic shocks, The Financial Times said on Monday.

headline.main: Bankers Worried Over European Bank Stress Tests
